Using notify rather than notifyAll in org.apache.hadoop.hbase.rsgroup.RSGroupInfoManagerImpl$ServerEventsListenerThread.serverChanged()

BugPattern.Details: This method calls notify() rather than notifyAll().  Java monitors are often used for multiple conditions.  Calling notify() only wakes up one thread, meaning that the thread woken up might not be the one waiting for the condition that the caller just satisfied.
This condition always produces the same result as the value of the involved variable that was narrowed before. Probably something else was meant or the condition can be removed.
